  "body": "## ðŸŽ‰ Description\r\n\r\nI would like to propose a variant of CappedCrowdsale allowing purchases over the cap, but automatically returning the value over back to the sender.\r\n\r\n- [x] ðŸ“ˆ This is a feature request.\r\n\r\n## ðŸ“ Details\r\n\r\nThe changes would probably involve:\r\n- creating a new extensible internal view _getWeiAmountToBook(msg.value) in Crowdsale.sol,\r\n- creating a new public view weiToCap(),\r\n- overriding _forwardFunds().\r\n\r\n## ðŸ”¢ Example snippets of code\r\n\r\nChanges in Crowdsale.sol:\r\n```\r\nfunction _getWeiAmountToBook(uint256 _weiAmount) \r\n    internal view returns (uint256)\r\n{\r\n    return _weiAmount;\r\n}\r\n\r\nfunction buyTokens(address _beneficiary) public payable {\r\n\r\n    uint256 weiAmount = _getWeiAmountToBook(msg.value);\r\n    ...\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nIn the new contract:\r\n```\r\nfunction _getWeiAmountToBook(uint256 _weiAmount)\r\n    internal view returns (uint256)\r\n{\r\n    uint256 _weiRaisedSum = weiRaised.add(_weiAmount);\r\n    if (_weiRaiseSum > cap) {\r\n        uint256 _weiOverCap = _weiRaisedSum.sub(cap);\r\n        return _weiAmount.sub(_weiOverCap); \r\n    } else {\r\n        return _weiAmount;\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n\r\nfunction _forwardFunds() internal {\r\n    uint256 _weiAmountToBook = _getWeiAmountToBook(msg.value);\r\n    wallet.transfer(_weiAmountToBook);\r\n    uint256 _weiOverCap = msg.value.sub(_weiAmountToBook);\r\n    if (_weiOverCap > 0) {\r\n        msg.sender.transfer(_weiOverCap);\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nPlease, let me know if this makes sense and if yes, I will provide a PR.",
