    "body": "My main opposition to this is that it's additional logic in the smart contract that could (should?) be part of the client. A client software for investing in a crowdsale should look at the cap, look at what's been raised, and then only allow someone to invest up to that amount. Now, this gets annoying towards the end of a popular crowdsale, sure, but I'm still not certain that this sort of logic belongs in the contract. ",
